Nos parecemos más de lo que creemos
<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/fernand0/16471973115" title="Bosque de columnas en una mezquita"><img src="https://c2.staticflickr.com/8/7316/16471973115_42c9d27fbb_m.jpg" width="240"  alt="Bosque de columnas en una mezquita" style="float:left; margin:5px"></a>
Me gustó leer <a href="https://medium.com/@tommauchline/15-things-i-learnt-about-islam-and-british-values-being-a-gay-boy-living-opposite-a-mosque-ebd385eb3113">15 things I learnt about Islam and British values being a gay boy living opposite a mosque</a> porque cuando nos referimos a 'gente normal' (entre comillas, sea lo que sea eso) todos nos parecemos bastante, independientemente de cultura, religión y modo de vida.
No niego que pueda haber diferencias, claro.

La excesiva cortesía ante los hechos extraordinarios:

<blockquote>
When confronted with something out of their comfort zone, like me and my boyfriend in full drag dancing down the road, muslims like all British people get flustered and over compensate with being overly polite -- a bit like Hugh Grant.
</blockquote>

Los vecinos musulmanes animando a casarse a una pareja gay:

<blockquote>
When finding out you have been dating your boyfriend for 5 years your muslim neighbours will be disgusted that you haven't proposed. You hear "get a civil partnership -- for your mothers sake" a lot.
</blockquote>

Y algunos principios generales:

<blockquote>
The media stories about islam meant that I was genuinely a little nervous about moving in across the road to a mosque. What I have learnt in the four years since I moved is that the ridiculousness of British culture is universal. We all love tea, are really polite and tut rather than saying something, no matter our religion.
</blockquote>

Creo que es de esas historias que vale la pena leer para aislarse un poco del tremendismo que solemos ver hacia la gente que no conocemos bien en nuestros muros de Facebook donde la humanidad va a terminar cualquier día de estos, si hacemos caso a las notas que vamos leyendo.

